record_data.record_plain_text: Cimarron Bend Assets, LLC Electric MBR Agreements Effective Date: September 3, 2020 Shared Facilities Agreement Option Code A EXHIBIT A Amended and Restated Shared Facilities Agreement, dated as of September 2, 2020, by and among Cimarron Bend Wind Project I, LLC, Cimarron Bend Wind Project II, LLC, Cimarron Bend Wind Project III, LLC, Enel Kansas, LLC, and Cimarron Bend Assets, LLC AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT among CIMARRON BEND ASSETS, LLC, CIMARRON BEND WIND PROJECT I, LLC CIMARRON BEND WIND PROJECT II, LLC, CIMARRON BEND WIND PROJECT III, LLC, and ENEL KANSAS, LLC September 2, 2020 AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is entered into as of September 2, 2020 (the “Effective Date”), by and among CIMARRON BEND WIND PROJECT I, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“CB1”), CIMARRON BEND WIND PROJECT II, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“CB2”) and CIMARRON BEND WIND PROJECT III, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“CB3” and together with CB1 and CB2, the “Users”), CIMARRON BEND ASSETS, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company formerly known as Cimarron Bend Wind Project, LLC (“Shareco”), and ENEL KANSAS, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (together with CB1, CB2, CB3 and Shareco, the “Parties” and each a “Party”). RECITALS: Each of CB1 and CB2 owns and operates a 200 MW installed capacity wind generation facility located in Clark County, Kansas on sites adjacent to one another that consist of wind turbine generators, foundations and towers and associated collection, interconnection and communication lines and related facilities and improvements (the “CB1 Project” and the “CB2 Project”, respectively). CB3 is developing a 200 MW wind generation facility located in Clark County, Kansas adjacent to the CB1 Project and CB2 Project which will consist of wind turbine generators, foundations and towers and associated collection, interconnection and communication lines and related facilities and improvements (collectively the “CB3 Project”; together with the CB1 Project and the CB2 Project, the “Projects”, and each, a “Project”). As of the date hereof, Shareco is a party to, and expects to be party to, certain agreements relating to the development, construction, operation, and maintenance of and creating a benefit for all of the Projects, and certain data, reports and property rights relating to and for the benefit of the Projects (the “Shareco Agreements”). As of the date hereof, CB1 is the holder of certain leasehold and easement rights (the “Underlying CB1 Shared Transmission Facilities Easement Rights”) on certain real property within the CB1 Project to be used as the site for or in connection with the Shared Transmission Facilities (defined below), which Underlying CB1 Shared Transmission Facilities Easement Rights and underlying encumbered real property (the “CB1 Shared Transmission Facilities Easement Area”), as further defined below and as listed on Exhibit B hereto and the CB1 Shared Transmission Facilities Easement Area is depicted on Exhibit B-1 hereto. Shareco is the owner of certain shared transmission facilities within the Shared Transmission Facilities Easement Area used for the interconnection of the Projects to the transmission system and for the transmission of the electric energy produced by the Projects to the point of interconnection with the transmission system, as further defined below and listed on Exhibit C hereto (the “Shared Transmission Facilities”). As of the date hereof, CB2 is also the holder of certain fee, leasehold and easement rights (the “Underlying CB2 Shared Facilities Easement Rights”) on certain real property within the CB2 Project to be used as the site for that portion of a substation, transmission and communication lines, and access roads for the benefit of the CB1 Project, CB2 Project and the CB3 Project to connect to the Shared Transmission Facilities, which Underlying CB2 Shared Facilities Easement Rights and underlying encumbered real property (the “CB2 Shared Facilities Easement Area”) are listed on Exhibit D hereto and the CB2 Shared Facilities Easement Area is depicted on Exhibit D-1 hereto. As of the date hereof, CB2 is the holder of certain leasehold and easement rights (the “Underlying CB2 Easement Rights”) on certain real property within the CB2 Project to be used as the site for an O M Building for the benefit and use of the CB1 Project, CB2 Project and CB3 Project (the “O M Building”), which Underlying CB2 Easement Rights and underlying encumbered real property (the “CB2 Easement Area”) are listed on Exhibit E hereto and the CB2 Easement Area is depicted on Exhibit E-1 hereto. As of the date hereof, CB2 is also the holder of certain leasehold and easement rights (the “Underlying CB2 T-Line Easement Rights”) on certain real property within the CB2 Project to be used as the site for transmission and communication lines, and access roads for the benefit of the CB3 Project to connect to the Shared Transmission Facilities, which Underlying CB2 T-Line Easement Rights and underlying encumbered real property have yet to be determined. The Parties have entered into that certain Shared Facilities Agreement, dated as of September 15, 2016, as amended by that certain First Amendment to Shared Facilities Agreement, dated as of December 21, 2016 (the “Original SFA”) in order to set forth their respective rights and obligations regarding the use, replacement of, and alterations to the Shared Assets and the Shareco Agreements, and to grant subeasement and sublease rights for the benefit of the Projects. The Parties now wish to amend and restate the Original SFA in its entirety, but subject to Section 2.2.1, to account for the development and operation of the CB3 Project. AGREEMENT: NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained in this Agreement and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is acknowledged, the Parties, subject to satisfaction of the conditions precedent set forth in Section 2.2.1, hereby amend, restate and replace the Original SFA in its entirety and agree as follows: DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION Definitions. Rules of Interpretation. Titles, captions and headings in this Agreement are inserted for convenience only and will not be used for the purposes of construing or interpreting this Agreement. In this Agreement, unless a clear, contrary intention appears: (i) the singular includes the plural and vice versa; (ii) reference to any Person includes such Person’s successors and assigns but, in the case of a Party, only if such successors and assigns are permitted by this Agreement (except to the extent explicitly provided otherwise), and reference to a Person in a particular capacity excludes such Person in any other capacity; (iii) reference to any gender includes each other gender; (iv) reference to any agreement (including this Agreement), document or instrument means such agreement, document or instrument as amended or modified and in effect from time to time in accordance with the terms thereof and, if applicable, the terms of this Agreement; (v) reference to any law means such law as amended, modified, codified or reenacted, in whole or in part, and in effect from time to time, including, if applicable, rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; (vi) reference to any Article or Section means such Article or Section of this Agreement, and references in any Article, Section or definition to any clause means such clause of such Article, Section or definition; (vii) “hereunder,” “hereof,” “hereto” and words of similar import will be deemed references to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular Article, Section or other provision of this Agreement; (viii) “including” (and with correlative meaning “include”) means including without limiting the generality of any description preceding such term; and (ix) relative to the determination of any period of time, “from” means “from and including”, “to” means “to but excluding” and “through” means “through and including”. Words and abbreviations not defined in this Agreement that have well-known technical or power industry meanings in the United States are used in this Agreement in accordance with those recognized meanings. This Agreement was negotiated and prepared by the Parties with advice of counsel to the extent deemed necessary by each Party. The Parties have agreed to the wording of this Agreement, and none of the provisions of this Agreement will be construed against one Party on the ground that such Party is the author of this Agreement or any part of this Agreement. TERM, CONTRIBUTION; CONDITIONS PRECEDENT AND RESTRICTIONS ON TERMINATION Effective Date. This Agreement will commence on the Effective Date and remain in full force and effect following the Effective Date until the first to occur of (a) the mutual written agreement of all the Users to terminate this Agreement, or (b) otherwise as provided under this Agreement. Conditions Precedent; CB3 Election to Commence Use. Conditions Precedent. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement or the Shareco LLCA, the Users’ and the Manager’s rights to use the Shared Assets shall be governed by the Original SFA until this Agreement shall have been filed with FERC for acceptance under section 205 of the Federal Power Act, and FERC has accepted this Agreement without imposing any condition that any Party considers unacceptable in its reasonable discretion, the satisfaction of such condition precedent shall be diligently pursued by the Users. [Reserved.] Right of CB3 to Commence Use of Shared Assets. The Parties acknowledge and agree that, (i) notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, the Original SFA or the Shareco LLCA, CB3’s right to use the Shared Assets under this Agreement or the Original SFA, as applicable, commenced upon the CB3 Use Commencement Date, (ii) CB3 shall neither have any liability hereunder or under the Original SFA, as applicable, for Shared Expenses, nor have any voting or consent rights hereunder or under the Original SFA, as applicable, and in either case, prior to the CB3 Use Commencement Date, except as expressly provided herein or in the Original SFA, and (iii) from and after the CB3 Use Commencement Date, CB3 shall be liable for its Use Percentage of the Shared Expenses and shall have such voting and consent rights as are provided the other Users hereunder and under the Original SFA, as applicable. Termination Subject to Prior FERC Approval. Notwithstanding anything expressed or implied herein to the contrary, from and after the fulfillment of the condition precedent set forth in Section 2.2.1 above, this Agreement may not be terminated without first obtaining an order from FERC permitting such termination or disconnection. GRANT OF EASEMENTS CB1 Shared Transmission Facilities Sub-easement. CB1 hereby irrevocably and unconditionally grants to each of Shareco, CB2 and CB3, and their respective successors and assigns, for the benefit of and appurtenant to the Shared Transmission Facilities, the CB2 Project and the CB3 Project, respectively, sub-easement and sublease rights over, across and under the CB1 Shared Transmission Facilities Easement Area for the purpose of constructing, operating and maintaining the CB1 Substation, overhead transmission lines and related facilities, including, without limitation, poles, crossarms, guy lines, anchors, conduit, fiber, cables, wires and related structures and ingress and egress access thereto as and to the extent such rights are granted to CB1 pursuant to the Underlying CB1 T-Line Easements Rights (the “CB1 Shared Facilities Sub-easement”). CB2 Shared Facilities Sub-easement. CB2 hereby irrevocably and unconditionally grants to Shareco, CB1, and CB3 and their respective successors and assigns, for the benefit of and appurtenant to the Shared Transmission Facilities, the CB1 Project and the CB3 Project, sub-easement and sublease rights over, across and under the CB2 Shared Facilities Easement Area for the purpose of constructing, operating and maintaining transmission lines and communication lines and related facilities, including, without limitation, poles, crossarms, guy lines, anchors, conduit, fiber, cables, wires and related structures and ingress and egress access thereto as and to the extent such rights are granted to CB2 pursuant to the Underlying CB2 Shared Facilities Easements Rights (the “CB2 Shared Facilities Sub-easement”). CB2 O M Sub-easement. CB2 hereby irrevocably and unconditionally grants to CB1, CB3 and Shareco, and their successors and assigns, for the benefit of and appurtenant to the Shared Transmission Facilities and CB1 Project, sub-easement and sublease rights over, across and under the CB2 Easement Area for the purpose of constructing, operating and maintaining, the ingress and egress access and use of and access to and from the O M Building, as and to the extent such rights are granted to CB2 pursuant to the Underlying CB2 Easements Rights (the “CB2 O M Sub-easement”). CB2 Transmission Line Sub-Easement. CB2 has granted CB3 sublease rights over, across and under certain tracts of land within the CB2 Project pursuant to that certain Wind Energy Sublease (Kansas – Cimarron Bend Wind Project III), dated as of August 6, 2020. SHARED ASSETS Shared Transmission Facilities; Shared Assets. After fulfillment of the conditions precedent set forth in Section 2.2.1, Shareco shall cause the completion of design and construction of the Shared Transmission Facilities. All Shared Assets will be owned by Shareco subject to the rights of the Users hereunder, and, pursuant to the Shareco O M Agreement, the Manager shall operate and maintain the Shared Assets. Access to Shared Assets. Each User and its Representatives shall have access to the Shared Assets (a) for inspection of the Shared Assets, and (b) in connection with the operation of the Shared Assets, all in accordance with this Agreement. Notwithstanding the foregoing, except in the event of an Emergency, each User shall provide no less than 24 hours’ prior notice to the Manager of its or any of its Representative’s intent to access the Shared Assets and the planned scope of work or other activities requiring such access, and each User shall provide no less than 48 hours’ prior notice to the Manager prior to accessing the Shared Assets. Each User and any User’s Representatives shall: (i) follow all applicable safety, security and site rules established by the Manager; and (ii) comply with all applicable real estate restrictions, applicable Law and Governmental Approvals when on the premises or accessing the Shared Assets, except to the extent that following any such rule would violate applicable Law. Manager will have access to the Shared Assets to perform any required maintenance and repairs of the Shared Assets, and prior notice to the Users or their Representatives shall not be required to repair the Shared Assets, but the Manager shall provide notice to, and coordinate with, the Users in accordance with the Shareco O M Agreement. No Interference, Cooperation; Quiet Enjoyment and Over-Burdening. A User’s use of the Shared Assets and the operation of its Project shall not interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Users of their respective rights to use the Shared Assets or the operation of its Project, except as specifically provided herein. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, including Section 7.13 below, each User hereby consents to the development and operation of each of the Projects owned by the other Users, and each User shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate the other User’s use of the Shared Assets for the benefit of the Projects as contemplated by this Agreement; provided that no User shall increase the nameplate capacity of its Project beyond 200MW without the prior written consent of the other Users. No User will use or permit the use of the Shared Assets in any manner that would create waste or nuisance, or that would jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Shared Assets or any Governmental Approval as to the Shared Assets or any Project, nor otherwise conduct or permit to be conducted operations on its Project Site which would have similar effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Shared Assets. All incremental costs and expenses associated with a User interconnecting a Project into the Shared Assets shall be for the account of, and paid for, by such User. The Manager shall arrange for such contracts and services as are necessary for such connection by a User, and Manager shall be compensated for its services and shall send invoices for such costs to such User pursuant to the Shareco O M Agreement.
